\ id nfoegqpcgzhctwbv
* "magma" means just a binary function (t -> t -> t)
* it is rather known as a type class:
	* class Magma t where
		* (<>) : t -> t -> t
* some famous potential properties of magmas
	* associative: (x <> y) <> z = x <> (y <> z)
		\ links-to internal zupoyjhzjznssfcb
	* commutative: x <> y = y <> x
	* idempotent: x <> x = x
	* absorb
		\ links-to internal oeltcgippeesnvsd
	* a value x is "idempotent" under a function f iff (f x x = x)
	* a function is idempotent iff all values are idempotent under it
* semigroup is the associative magma
	\ links-to internal eovnsnrjngyuihhx
* neutral element
	\ links-to internal syexzvqvirwlpspt
* absorber element
	\ links-to internal juchknabrgkcpwyb